  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nVersion: 1.10.13-stable\r\nArchitecture: amd64\r\nGo Version: go1.18.1\r\nOperating System: linux\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nWhen loading a configuration, `cache` should stay the same for whatever mode.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\nWhen using a configuration, running the `js` command has `cache` set to 1024 (default value for command line), while without command it will be set to 4096 (default value for mainnet full node).\r\n\r\nThis can be reflected by different values in `triecache/metadata.bin`, which is elaborated in the next section.\r\n\r\n`cache` won't be set to 4096 when no config file is loaded.\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n\r\n```\r\necho >> sample.js\r\ngeth dumpconfig /tmp/gethconfig.toml\r\ngeth --config /tmp/gethconfig.toml --datadir /tmp/jscommand js sample.js\r\ntimeout -s INT 5s geth --config /tmp/gethconfig.toml --datadir /tmp/nocommand\r\ndiff /tmp/jscommand/geth/triecache/metadata.bin /tmp/nocommand/geth/triecache/metadata.bin\r\n```\r\nShould give\r\nBinary files /tmp/jscommand/geth/triecache/metadata.bin and /tmp/nocommand/geth/triecache/metadata.bin differ\r\n\r\nThe value in `metadata.bin`, according to [this line of code](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/86d547707965685cef732aa28c15e6811ea98408/cmd/utils/flags.go#L1651) should be 0x5 and 0x14, respectively.\r\n",
